The Olubadan of Ibadan in Oyo State, Oba Saliu Adetunji, has promoted 14 chiefs including Chief Wasiu Ajimobi, brother of former Governor Abiola Ajimobi. The News Agency of Nigeria  reports that they were promoted on Friday at an installation ceremony held at the Popoyemoja palace of the monarch in Ibadan. READ ALSO: DSS nabs mastermind of Buhari’s ‘fake wedding’ NAN reports that Ajimobi, formerly Aare Onibon Balogun, is now Lagunna Balogun of Ibadanland. The Olubadan commended the newly elevated chiefs for their contributions to the development of Ibadanland, urging them not to relent in supporting developmental projects in ancient city. (NAN)